  /*
    {{page-title 'Admin Tasks'}}
  <h1>Admin Tasks</h1>
  
  
  
  {{#if this.status}}
  <p>The upgrade/deploy task may take a couple minutes.  The status will update below.  Be sure to pay attention to any errors displayed.</p>
  
  <hr>
  
  <pre id="manageLog" class="console">  <AnsiFormat @text={{this.status}} /></pre>
  
  <hr>
  
  <p>When the status says the task is done, you can <button {{on 'click' this.returnToManage}} class="btn-link">return to the manage screen.</button></p>
  
  
  {{else}}
  
  <h2>Upgrade the Game</h2>        
  
  <p>This button will take upgrade your game to the latest Ares version.</p>
  
  <div class="alert alert-warning">
    Before starting the upgrade, be sure that:
    
    <ul>
      <li>You <b>do not</b> have any custom code changes -or- you have already resolved any merge conflicts with your code/fork.</li>
      <li>You have checked the <a href="https://github.com/AresMUSH/aresmush/releases">Release Notes</a> for any special upgrade instructions associated with the patch.  If you're skipping versions (e.g., from version 2 to version 5) be sure to check <b>each</b> of the release notes.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  
      <p><button class="btn btn-primary" {{on 'click' (fn this.upgrade 'all')}}>Upgrade</button></p>
  
  
  <a data-bs-toggle="collapse" href="#advancedUpgrade" class="btn btn-secondary btn-collapse">Advanced</a>
  <div id="advancedUpgrade" class="card-collapse collapse">
  
     <div class="card card-default">
        <div class="card-body">
  
          <p>Coders - you can run the two pieces of the upgrade process separately.</p>
          <ul>
            <li><button {{on 'click' (fn this.upgrade 'start')}} class="btn-link">Start Upgrade</button> - grabs the latest code changes from GitHub.</li>
            <li><button {{on 'click' (fn this.upgrade 'finish')}} class="btn-link">Finish Upgrade</button> - reloads and redeploys the code.</li>
          </ul>
          
        </div>
    </div>
    
  
  </div>
  
  
  <p><hr></p>
  
  <h2>Idle Sweep</h2>
  
  <p>The idle sweep lets you prune characters whose players have left the game. See <LinkTo @route="help-topic" @model="idle" target="_blank">Idle Sweep</LinkTo> for help.</p>
    
  <LinkTo @route="idle" class="btn btn-primary">Idle Sweep</LinkTo>
  
  <p><hr></p>
  
  
  
  <h2>Banned Sites</h2>
  
  <p>The ban system can help you block troublesome players from the game. See <LinkTo @route="help-topic" @model="ban" target="_blank">Bans</LinkTo> for help.</p>
    
  <LinkTo @route="banned" class="btn btn-primary">Manage Bans</LinkTo>
  
  <p><hr></p>
  
  <h2>Deploy the Website</h2>
      
      
      <p>This button will redeploy the website.  You need to redeploy if you make custom web portal code changes.  Doing an upgrade will redeploy automatically.</p>
          
      <p><button class="btn btn-primary" {{on 'click' this.deploy}}>Redeploy Website</button></p>
  
  
  <p><hr></p>
  
  <h2>Backups</h2>
  
  <p>To learn more about game backups, see <a href="https://aresmush.com/tutorials/manage/backups.html" target="_blank">Backing Up the Game</a>.</p>
  
  <p><hr></p>
          
  <h2>Shut Down the Game</h2>
  
      <div class="alert alert-danger">
          <p>This button will shut down your game. It does the same thing as the in-game 'shutdown' command.  You will have to log into the server shell to restart the game.</p>
      </div>
          
          <p><button class="btn btn-danger" {{on 'click' this.shutdown}}>Shutdown</button></p>
  {{/if}}
  
  
  
  {{outlet}}
  */
